FuncDef: The display service-type config command displays CPU service types on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
CLIs: display service-type config [ slot <slot-id> [ { card <card-id> | engine <engine-id> } ] ]

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the slot ID of a service board.
The value is a string of 1 to 15 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.

Specifies the CPU ID of a subcard on a service board.
The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 1.

Specifies the CPU ID of a service board. This parameter takes effect only on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
The value is an integer equal 0 for VSUF-80.
The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 1 for VSUF-160,VSUI-160-E,VSUI-400A/VSUI-400.
The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 3 for VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-E.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The display service-type config command displays CPU service types on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
